article.headline: Maine 73, Stony Brook 60
article.story: ORONO, Maine (AP) -- Kevin Reed was 5-of-8 from 3-point range and scored 17 points to lead Maine to a 73-60 victory over Stony Brook on Sunday. Maine (7-4, 2-0 America East) scored the game's first 13 points, holding Stony Brook scoreless for 5:30. Stony Brook (5-6, 0-2) closed within 26-21 by halftime, but the Black Bears started the second half with a 9-2 run. Ernest Turner had 14 points, while Chris Bruff added 13 and Mark Flavin 10 for Maine. Antwan Hardy had 20 points for the Seawolves, while Cori Spencer added 11, all in the second half after he sat out most of the opening 20 minutes with foul trouble.
